-- Germany Backs Its Wind Industry in Move Toward Asia, U.S. Growth
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-09-18T11:05:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-18/germany-backs-its-wind-industry-in-move-toward-asia-u-s-growth.html
Germany is backing domestic wind-
power producers as they seek to expand in markets including the
U.S., Japan and  Mexico .  Deputy Economy Minister Stefan Kapferer opened a German
 chamber of commerce  event in  Tokyo  last week as part of a trip
by wind-company executives to Japan, the ministry said today in
a statement. Visits to the U.S., Mexico,  South Africa , Egypt and
Indonesia are also planned this year and next, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
 snicola2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
